# Keep the Docker build context small. Home's image uses the repo root
# as its context (so ../CLI can be copied into the build). The Dockerfile
# only COPYs Home/ and CLI/, but anything not ignored here still gets
# uploaded to the Docker daemon on every build.
.git
.github
node_modules
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.next
**/.vite
**/.turbo
**/.cache
**/coverage
App/data
Home/client/public/genosyn
Home/client/public/install.sh
